from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

def scale_data(df, columns):
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    df_scaled = df.copy()
    df_scaled[columns] = scaler.fit_transform(df[columns])
    return df_scaled

cols_to_scale = data.drop("TARGET", axis = 1).columns.to_list()

def decision_tree_with_parameters3(df, target_column, feature_columns, criterion='gini', max_depth=None, min_samples_split=2, min_samples_leaf=1, class_weight=None):
    X = df[feature_columns]
    y = df[target_column]
    
    # Split the data into training and testing sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y)
    
    # Initialize the Decision Tree classifier with specified parameters
    dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion=criterion, max_depth=max_depth, min_samples_split=min_samples_split, min_samples_leaf=min_samples_leaf, class_weight=class_weight)
    
    # Fit the model
    dt.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    # Make predictions on training data
    y_train_pred = dt.predict(X_train)
    
    # Evaluate the model on training data
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_precision = precision_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_recall = recall_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_f1 = f1_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    
    # Make predictions on test data
    y_test_pred = dt.predict(X_test)
    
    # Evaluate the model on test data
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    
    print("Training Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {train_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {train_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {train_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {train_f1}")
    
    print("\nTest Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {test_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {test_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {test_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {test_f1}")
    
    # Confusion matrix for training data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_train = confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_train, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g', 
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'], 
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Training Data')
    plt.show()
    
    # Confusion matrix for test data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_test = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_test, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g', 
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'], 
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Test Data')
    plt.show()

    print("\nClassification Report - Training Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_train, y_train_pred))

    print("\nClassification Report - Test Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred))

from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

def decision_tree_with_parameters_smote(df, target_column, feature_columns, criterion='gini', max_depth=None, min_samples_split=2, min_samples_leaf=1, class_weight=None):
    X = df[feature_columns]
    y = df[target_column]
    
    # Split the data into training and testing sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=10, stratify=y)
    
    # Apply SMOTE to balance the classes only on the training data
    smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
    X_train_smote, y_train_smote = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    
    # Initialize the Decision Tree classifier with specified parameters
    dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion=criterion, max_depth=max_depth, min_samples_split=min_samples_split, min_samples_leaf=min_samples_leaf, class_weight=class_weight)
    
    # Fit the model
    dt.fit(X_train_smote, y_train_smote)
    
    # Make predictions on training data
    y_train_pred = dt.predict(X_train_smote)
    
    # Evaluate the model on training data
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_smote, y_train_pred)
    train_precision = precision_score(y_train_smote, y_train_pred)
    train_recall = recall_score(y_train_smote, y_train_pred)
    train_f1 = f1_score(y_train_smote, y_train_pred)
    
    # Make predictions on test data
    y_test_pred = dt.predict(X_test)
    
    # Evaluate the model on test data
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    
    print("Training Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {train_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {train_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {train_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {train_f1}")
    
    print("\nTest Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {test_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {test_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {test_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {test_f1}")
    
    # Confusion matrix for training data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_train = confusion_matrix(y_train_smote, y_train_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_train, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g', 
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'], 
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Training Data')
    plt.show()
    
    # Confusion matrix for test data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_test = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_test, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g', 
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'], 
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Test Data')
    plt.show()

    print("\nClassification Report - Training Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_train_smote, y_train_pred))

    print("\nClassification Report - Test Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred))

XG Boost¶

In [117]:
import xgboost as xgb
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def xgboost_with_parameters(df, target_column, feature_columns, scale_pos_weight=1):
    X = df[feature_columns]
    y = df[target_column]

    # Split the data into training and testing sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=10, stratify=y)

    # Initialize the XGBoost classifier with specified parameters
    model = xgb.XGBClassifier(scale_pos_weight=scale_pos_weight, random_state=42)

    # Fit the model
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    # Make predictions on training data
    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)

    # Evaluate the model on training data
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_precision = precision_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_recall = recall_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_f1 = f1_score(y_train, y_train_pred)

    # Make predictions on test data
    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)

    # Evaluate the model on test data
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_test_pred)

    print("Training Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {train_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {train_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {train_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {train_f1}")

    print("\nTest Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {test_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {test_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {test_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {test_f1}")

    # Confusion matrix for training data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_train = confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_train, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g',
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'],
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Training Data')
    plt.show()

    # Confusion matrix for test data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_test = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_test, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g',
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'],
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Test Data')
    plt.show()

    print("\nClassification Report - Training Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_train, y_train_pred))

    print("\nClassification Report - Test Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred))

def xgboost_with_parameters_smote(df, target_column, feature_columns, scale_pos_weight=1):
    X = df[feature_columns]
    y = df[target_column]

    # Split the data into training and testing sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=10, stratify=y)

    # Apply SMOTE only on the training data to balance the classes
    smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
    X_train_smote, y_train_smote = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)

    # Initialize the XGBoost classifier with specified parameters
    model = xgb.XGBClassifier(scale_pos_weight=scale_pos_weight, random_state=42)

    # Fit the model on SMOTE-transformed training data
    model.fit(X_train_smote, y_train_smote)

    # Make predictions on training data
    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)

    # Evaluate the model on training data
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_precision = precision_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_recall = recall_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
    train_f1 = f1_score(y_train, y_train_pred)

    # Make predictions on test data
    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)

    # Evaluate the model on test data
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_test_pred)
    test_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_test_pred)

    print("Training Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {train_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {train_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {train_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {train_f1}")

    print("\nTest Performance:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {test_accuracy}")
    print(f"Precision: {test_precision}")
    print(f"Recall: {test_recall}")
    print(f"F1 Score: {test_f1}")

    # Confusion matrix for training data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_train = confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_train, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g',
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'],
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Training Data')
    plt.show()

    # Confusion matrix for test data
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cm_test = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm_test, annot=True, cmap='Blues', fmt='g',
                xticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'],
                yticklabels=['Class 0', 'Class 1'])
    plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
    plt.ylabel('True labels')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Test Data')
    plt.show()

    print("\nClassification Report - Training Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_train, y_train_pred))

    print("\nClassification Report - Test Data:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred))
